{"履修期": "春学期", "主な教授言語": "英語", "授業目的": "Please refer to the English section.", "到達目標": "Please refer to the English section.", "特記事項": "", "関連科目": "", "授業の概要・背景": "<a name=\"OLE_LINK59\" style=\"font-size:medium;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" times=\"times\" new=\"new\" roman\",serif;\"=\"roman',serif;'\" style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:;\">Skills Based English (TOEIC) is a once-a-week course designed to develop learners’ ability in taking the TOEIC test. Students will participate in vocabulary building activities, practice test questions and learn test strategies. This will help students to improve their TOEIC test score and build strong language skills for the future.</span></a>", "授業方法": "All classes are expected to be taught face-to-face. Google Classroom will be used for some course information and assignment submissions. Therefore, students will NEED access to a computer at home or use a school computer lab to be able to properly complete and submit assignments. Desktop, laptop, notebook, Macbook, etc, are fine. Students should also have a Google account and sign up for Google Drive and Google Classroom (both are free).Learners who miss tests and do not have an official absence will not have any opportunity to retake the test.This course is taught in English. Students should communicate with the teacher in English. Assignments may require the use of a computer and online sites.Additionally, this class includes collaboration and regular pairwork. All members are expected to support each other.&nbsp;", "トピック": {"第1回": ["<span style=\"font-size:13.3333px;\">ALL SESSION INFORMATION IS SUBJECT TO CHANGE AT THE TEACHER'S DISCRETION</span><div><span style=\"font-size:13.3333px;\">【Startup Week】URL:&nbsp;https://kwansei.jp.panopto.com/Panopto/Pages/Viewer.aspx?id=56619921-24f0-4c7c-8730-b41c00846c45</span></div><div><span style=\"font-size:13.3333px;\">\"Online class（On-demand format）\"/《120minutes》Watch the instruction video then complete the practice TOEIC test.</span><